The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning systems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of attention mechanisms is a common technique in deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the coordination and adaptation of agents, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The presence of malicious agents and the need for fault tolerance suggests a focus on security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning in multi-agent systems suggests a connection to control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY).
